3022// Font runtime data and rendering
3023// ImFontAtlas automatically loads a default embedded font for you when you call GetTexDataAsAlpha8() or GetTexDataAsRGBA32().
3024struct ImFont
3025{
3026 // Members: Hot ~20/24 bytes (for CalcTextSize)
3027 ImVector<float> IndexAdvanceX; // 12-16 // out // // Sparse. Glyphs->AdvanceX in a directly indexable way (cache-friendly for CalcTextSize functions which only this this info, and are often bottleneck in large UI).
3028 float FallbackAdvanceX; // 4 // out // = FallbackGlyph->AdvanceX
3029 float FontSize; // 4 // in // // Height of characters/line, set during loading (don't change after loading)
3030
3031 // Members: Hot ~28/40 bytes (for CalcTextSize + render loop)
3032 ImVector<ImWchar> IndexLookup; // 12-16 // out // // Sparse. Index glyphs by Unicode code-point.
3033 ImVector<ImFontGlyph> Glyphs; // 12-16 // out // // All glyphs.
3034 const ImFontGlyph* FallbackGlyph; // 4-8 // out // = FindGlyph(FontFallbackChar)
3035
3036 // Members: Cold ~32/40 bytes
3037 ImFontAtlas* ContainerAtlas; // 4-8 // out // // What we has been loaded into
3038 const ImFontConfig* ConfigData; // 4-8 // in // // Pointer within ContainerAtlas->ConfigData
3039 short ConfigDataCount; // 2 // in // ~ 1 // Number of ImFontConfig involved in creating this font. Bigger than 1 when merging multiple font sources into one ImFont.
3040 ImWchar FallbackChar; // 2 // out // = FFFD/'?' // Character used if a glyph isn't found.
3041 ImWchar EllipsisChar; // 2 // out // = '...'/'.'// Character used for ellipsis rendering.
3042 short EllipsisCharCount; // 1 // out // 1 or 3
3043 float EllipsisWidth; // 4 // out // Width
3044 float EllipsisCharStep; // 4 // out // Step between characters when EllipsisCount > 0
3045 bool DirtyLookupTables; // 1 // out //
3046 float Scale; // 4 // in // = 1.f // Base font scale, multiplied by the per-window font scale which you can adjust with SetWindowFontScale()
3047 float Ascent, Descent; // 4+4 // out // // Ascent: distance from top to bottom of e.g. 'A' [0..FontSize]
3048 int MetricsTotalSurface;// 4 // out // // Total surface in pixels to get an idea of the font rasterization/texture cost (not exact, we approximate the cost of padding between glyphs)
3049 ImU8 Used4kPagesMap[(IM_UNICODE_CODEPOINT_MAX+1)/4096/8]; // 2 bytes if ImWchar=ImWchar16, 34 bytes if ImWchar==ImWchar32. Store 1-bit for each block of 4K codepoints that has one active glyph. This is mainly used to facilitate iterations across all used codepoints.
3050
3051 // Methods
3052 IMGUI_API ImFont();
3053 IMGUI_API ~ImFont();
3054 IMGUI_API const ImFontGlyph*FindGlyph(ImWchar c) const;
3055 IMGUI_API const ImFontGlyph*FindGlyphNoFallback(ImWchar c) const;
3056 float GetCharAdvance(ImWchar c) const { return ((int)c < IndexAdvanceX.Size) ? IndexAdvanceX[(int)c] : FallbackAdvanceX; }
3057 bool IsLoaded() const { return ContainerAtlas != NULL; }
3058 const char* GetDebugName() const { return ConfigData ? ConfigData->Name : "<unknown>"; }
3059
3060 // 'max_width' stops rendering after a certain width (could be turned into a 2d size). FLT_MAX to disable.
3061 // 'wrap_width' enable automatic word-wrapping across multiple lines to fit into given width. 0.0f to disable.
3062 IMGUI_API ImVec2 CalcTextSizeA(float size, float max_width, float wrap_width, const char* text_begin, const char* text_end = NULL, const char** remaining = NULL) const; // utf8
3063 IMGUI_API const char* CalcWordWrapPositionA(float scale, const char* text, const char* text_end, float wrap_width) const;
3064 IMGUI_API void RenderChar(ImDrawList* draw_list, float size, const ImVec2& pos, ImU32 col, ImWchar c) const;
3065 IMGUI_API void RenderText(ImDrawList* draw_list, float size, const ImVec2& pos, ImU32 col, const ImVec4& clip_rect, const char* text_begin, const char* text_end, float wrap_width = 0.0f, bool cpu_fine_clip = false) const;
3066
3067 // [Internal] Don't use!
3068 IMGUI_API void BuildLookupTable();
3069 IMGUI_API void ClearOutputData();
3070 IMGUI_API void GrowIndex(int new_size);
3071 IMGUI_API void AddGlyph(const ImFontConfig* src_cfg, ImWchar c, float x0, float y0, float x1, float y1, float u0, float v0, float u1, float v1, float advance_x);
3072 IMGUI_API void AddRemapChar(ImWchar dst, ImWchar src, bool overwrite_dst = true); // Makes 'dst' character/glyph points to 'src' character/glyph. Currently needs to be called AFTER fonts have been built.
3073 IMGUI_API void SetGlyphVisible(ImWchar c, bool visible);
3074 IMGUI_API bool IsGlyphRangeUnused(unsigned int c_begin, unsigned int c_last);
3075};

3081// Flags stored in ImGuiViewport::Flags, giving indications to the platform backends.
3082enum ImGuiViewportFlags_
3083{
3084 ImGuiViewportFlags_None = 0,
3085 ImGuiViewportFlags_IsPlatformWindow = 1 << 0, // Represent a Platform Window
3086 ImGuiViewportFlags_IsPlatformMonitor = 1 << 1, // Represent a Platform Monitor (unused yet)
3087 ImGuiViewportFlags_OwnedByApp = 1 << 2, // Platform Window: is created/managed by the application (rather than a dear imgui backend)
3088};
3089
3090// - Currently represents the Platform Window created by the application which is hosting our Dear ImGui windows.
3091// - In 'docking' branch with multi-viewport enabled, we extend this concept to have multiple active viewports.
3092// - In the future we will extend this concept further to also represent Platform Monitor and support a "no main platform window" operation mode.
3093// - About Main Area vs Work Area:
3094// - Main Area = entire viewport.
3095// - Work Area = entire viewport minus sections used by main menu bars (for platform windows), or by task bar (for platform monitor).
3096// - Windows are generally trying to stay within the Work Area of their host viewport.
3097struct ImGuiViewport
3098{
3099 ImGuiViewportFlags Flags; // See ImGuiViewportFlags_
3100 ImVec2 Pos; // Main Area: Position of the viewport (Dear ImGui coordinates are the same as OS desktop/native coordinates)
3101 ImVec2 Size; // Main Area: Size of the viewport.
3102 ImVec2 WorkPos; // Work Area: Position of the viewport minus task bars, menus bars, status bars (>= Pos)
3103 ImVec2 WorkSize; // Work Area: Size of the viewport minus task bars, menu bars, status bars (<= Size)
3104
3105 // Platform/Backend Dependent Data
3106 void* PlatformHandleRaw; // void* to hold lower-level, platform-native window handle (under Win32 this is expected to be a HWND, unused for other platforms)
3107
3108 ImGuiViewport() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
3109
3110 // Helpers
3111 ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2(Pos.x + Size.x * 0.5f, Pos.y + Size.y * 0.5f); }
3112 ImVec2 GetWorkCenter() const { return ImVec2(WorkPos.x + WorkSize.x * 0.5f, WorkPos.y + WorkSize.y * 0.5f); }
3113};
